{
  "stem": "2004.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, what we used to do is we were picked up by a truck at a certain point every day, approximately-- I believe it must've been around 4 o'clock in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we worked for, I think it was 10 hours.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And every day, we were brought back in the morning, back home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then we could sleep and whatever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At 4 o'clock, we had to be back at the designated place and go back for the next day's work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, in August of 1942, while we were working in that lumber yard, we saw an entire fleet of trucks loaded.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was the German SS going towards Gorlice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, this lumber yard was approximately-- was in the suburbs of Gorlice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We saw them at night, somewhere around 8:00, 9 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were all going en masse towards Gorlice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we expected-- we heard some rumors that they were going to liquidate the ghetto in Gorlice, and all the Jews were going to be taken away and sent out.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know where, but they were going to be sent out somewhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when it came time to quit, we never came to the truck, but we hid in the lumber yard.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was lots of sawdust there, so we hid-- we each of us hid and somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We scattered around it, and we hid, hoping that we would never be found.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in the morning, we were hoping to escape, not to go back because the Poles told us that they're liquidating-- the Poles that were working with us there told us that they already got the news that there were-- that there was going to be-- that ghetto in Gorlice was going to be liquidated.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "However, early in the morning, I myself fell asleep.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
